<?php	if ($_POST) {		update_option('isob_option_1', $_POST['isob_option_1']);		update_option('isob_option_2', $_POST['isob_option_2']);		}	$banner_orientation = get_option('isob_option_1');	$banner_link = get_option('isob_option_2');	?><div class="wrap"><h2><?php print ISOB_PUGIN_NAME ." ". ISOB_CURRENT_VERSION. "<small>(Build ".ISOB_CURRENT_BUILD.")</small>"; ?></h2><? if ($_POST) {?>	<div id="message" class="updated below-h2"><p>Settings updated.</p></div><? } ?><script type="text/javascript">	function setImg(option){		if (option == 1) {			document.getElementById('bannerexampleimg').src="<?php echo WP_PLUGIN_URL .'/'. ISOB_PLUGIN_DIRECTORY; ?>/images/example-left.jpg";		} else {			document.getElementById('bannerexampleimg').src="<?php echo WP_PLUGIN_URL .'/'. ISOB_PLUGIN_DIRECTORY; ?>/images/example-right.jpg";					}	}</script><form method="post">	<?php settings_fields( 'isob-settings-group' ); ?>		<h3>Banner Orientation</h3>	<table class="form-table">		<tr>			<td valign="top">				<p><input onchange="setImg(1);" type="radio" id="rad1" name="isob_option_1" value="1" <?php if ($banner_orientation == '1'){ echo 'checked="checked"';} ?> />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <label for="rad1">top LEFT</label></p>				<p><input onchange="setImg(2);" type="radio" id="rad2" name="isob_option_1" value="2" <?php if ($banner_orientation == '2'){ echo 'checked="checked"';} ?> />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <label for="rad2">top RIGHT</label></p>			</td>			<td>				<?php if ($banner_orientation == '2'){?>					<img id="bannerexampleimg" src="<?php echo WP_PLUGIN_URL .'/'. ISOB_PLUGIN_DIRECTORY; ?>/images/example-right.jpg" />				<?php } else { ?>					<img id="bannerexampleimg" src="<?php echo WP_PLUGIN_URL .'/'. ISOB_PLUGIN_DIRECTORY; ?>/images/example-left.jpg" />								<?php } ?>							</td>		</tr>	</table>	<br />		<h3>Your banner will link to:</h3>	<table class="form-table">		<tr>			<td valign="top">				<p><input type="radio" id="url1" name="isob_option_2" value="1" <?php if ($banner_link == '1'){ echo 'checked="checked"';} ?> />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <label for="url1">Banner project page: occupybanner.wordpress.com - <strong>recommended</strong></label> (<a href="#why">why?</a>)</p>				<p><input type="radio" id="url2" name="isob_option_2" value="2" <?php if ($banner_link == '2'){ echo 'checked="checked"';} ?> />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <label for="url2">OccupyWallSt.org</label></p>				<p><input type="radio" id="url3" name="isob_option_2" value="3" <?php if ($banner_link == '3'){ echo 'checked="checked"';} ?> />&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; <label for="url3">OccupyTogether.org</label></p>												<br />				<p class="submit">					<input type="submit" class="button-primary" value="<?php _e('Save Changes') ?>" />				</p>							</td>		</tr>	</table></form><br /><hr /><br />	<h2>About Occupy Wall Street</h2>	<p><strong>Q: What is the Occupy Everywhere movement?</strong><br />Occupy Wall Street/Occupy Everywhere is an ongoing series of demonstrations that began in New York City and have spread to major cities across the United States. These are peaceful protests against social and economic inequality, corporate greed, and the influence of corporate money and lobbyists on government.</p>	<p>For more information please visit <a target="_blank" href="http://occupywallst.org">occupywallst.org</a> and <a target="_blank" href="http://occupytogether.org">occupytogether.org</a>.</p>		<br />		<h2>About this banner project</h2>	<p><strong>Q: How does this banner work?</strong><br />This plugin places a simple banner saying "I Support the Occupy Movement" on your site.</p>	<p>The banner itself links back to the <a href="http://occupybanner.wordpress.com/">banner project page</a> with information and links on the Occupy movement and instructions for getting and using the banner. The goal here is to make it super easy for people to put this banner on their sites and thus spread awareness and participation in the Occupy movement.</p>	<a name="why"></a>	<p><strong>Q: Why does the banner link to the banner project page by default, rather than directly to the Occupy Wall St site?</strong><br />As of this version, I have not received a reply from the Occupy Wall St. site about hosting this banner project there. In order to spread the banners, the banner needs to link to a place where people can get the banner for themselves. I will gladly give this all to the Occupy Wall St site if/when they decide to host the project page and banner instructions there.</p>		<br />	<h2>Help</h2>		<p><strong>Q: The banner image isn't appearing.</strong><br />Be sure the plugin's <em>image</em> folder is readable. Check <em>plugins/i-support-occupy-banner/images</em> and set permissions to <em>755</em></p>	<p><strong>Other questions?</strong> <a href="http://jeffcouturier.com/occupybanner/">Contact the author</a>.</p>	<br /><hr /><br />	<p><em>part of the <strong>I Support the Occupy Movement banner project</strong> by <a href="http://jeffcouturier.com/occupybanner/">Jeff Couturier</a></em></p>	<div style="height:300px"></div></div>